description:
Bug 3666 - Code Completion Hungry code assist (1GDRYW5)

Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature eats too much code. In the given example, to make the program correct, a parameter needs to be added to the baz call in the bar method.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Open the enclosed class.
2. Go to the bar method.
3. Add a parameter to the baz call to make the program correct.

Observed Behavior:
The code is changed to:

baz(x.foo().foo())

Expected Behavior:
I would rather it gave me:

baz(x.foo(), x.foo())

public class X {
    void bar(X x) {
        baz(x.foo());
    }

    int foo() {
        return 5;
    }

    void baz(int i, int j) {
    }
}
